ratings.comment: He's such a good professor- extremely passionate about subject, just overestimates at times how much students can comprehend. The material can be hard especially if you are just taking class to fulfill science requirement.

Prof. Martin is a great professor, really passionate and just a really good guy. Lectures are kind of fast paced, and the course is really physics heavy which wasn't my favorite, but he made it as interesting as weather can be. The class is kinda boring unless you're really interested in weather but it was still a good physical science requirement.

Professor Martin shows up to lecture everyday ready to get you excited about the weather. I took the honors section, and felt incredibly well supported the whole semester. Exams aren't too difficult, all MC. Homework is more challenging but doable. Lecture matches the textbook but is worth going to because he's great.

Prof. Martin is honestly one of my favorite lecturers that I've had during my time in college so far. I really like going to his class because the cadence with which he speaks is fantastic for keeping my attention and for taking notes. His textbook is concise, and technically optional, but is extremely useful for studying.
